    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Business enterprises owned and operated by members who use the enterprises' services and share the financial benefits. The first consumer cooperative store was established in Rochdale, England, in 1844, and most are still modeled after the original principles.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
